ily docs.","The provider exposed useful controls for content mode, focus, character budgets, domain policy, source type, and GitHub category."],"weaknesses":["Combined multi-domain sourcePolicy searches returned zero results twice, requiring split follow-up searches.","Some GitHub-category Tavily search results included unrelated GitHub repositories after the primary result, creating avoidable noise.","firecrawl_scrape responses were large and the normalized evidence for scrape calls was thin compared with the raw markdown content."],"notableFailures":[{"category":"direct fix and needs no further changes","failure":"The initial all-provider constrained search returned zero results.","fix":"Split searches by provider/domain and used more targeted queries."},{"category":"direct fix and needs no further changes","failure":"The broad Tavily constrained search returned zero results.","fix":"Searched GitHub and docs.tavily.com separately, then scraped the Tavily benchmark repository."},{"category":"fixed but could benefit from cleaner/simpler implementation with an architectural change","failure":"Known-page scrapes produced very large raw responses while normalized scrape evidence retained little useful excerpt text.","fix":"Used the raw markdown evidence saved by the harness, but the benchmark normalizer could be improved to retain bounded scrape excerpts for scoring."}],"confidence":0.88},"artifact":"report.json"}
